race.comment: VARAZZE (8) deep into her preparation and shapes as the main danger with a string of minor placings. Stalked the speed when third over 1000m at Kempsey. Fitter now and goes well at this track. NULKABA STAR (1) near his peak for this and the winkers come off. Struggled to see the 1250m out when fifth at Kempsey after showing good early speed. Will push forward and figure prominently. BUZZ SAW (2) showing ability in his first prep and only needs an ounce of luck to get off the mark. Worked hard from the wide gate when a tough second over 1000m at Kempsey. Key jockey change and must respect. VANTORIX (11) two-year-old gelding by Captivant from Miss Loren on debut for the Jenny Graham yard. Looked good in his only trial win over 1000m and maps well.
